 time, but since he stubbornly refused to answer it that too finally died down. They stopped taking any notice of Luzhin and did not speak to him, and even the sole quiet boy in the class (the sort there is in every class, just as there are invariably a fat boy, a strong boy and a wit) steered clear of him, afraid of sharing his despicable condition.

This same quiet boy, who six ears later, in the beginning of World War One, received the St. George Cross for an extremely dangerous reconnaisance